Lower level lends itself to additional family room for movies or games & has another 1/2 bath. Two car attached garage & just steps from the community pool! Check out virtual tour!

description: For sale: $775,000. Recently updated home move-in ready! high ceilings and expansive windows throughout home provide open feeling to wooded backyard. Lot's of privacy on a quiet cul de sac street with other luxury homes in Mendota Heights. Easy flow on first floor living from master bedroom to living and dining room to large kitchen and laundry/mudroom. Unique architecture of Home makes comfortable living spaces. New maintenance free deck to enjoy sunsets over Mississippi Bluffs and garden area. Tastefully finished basement allows for relaxed family time as well. Plenty of comfortable bedrooms downstairs for sleeping, office or work out rooms. Heated triple car garage with negotiable sports car lift.  Many newer updates are Hi efficient furnace, water heater, Front load washer and dryer, driveway, garage overhead doors. Walkout lower level patio to hot tub. Ring security also included. Minutes from Minneapolis Airport, downtown St. Paul and easy freeway access.

For sale: $935,000. Beautiful home on a small hill overlooking beautiful 1-acre grassy outlot (owned by neighborhood) with terrific entertaining spaces and a private, landscaped backyard featuring 18'x36' in-ground heated pool (new liner 2019, newer pool heater) and 14' diameter screened gazebo. This home features a first-floor master suite, on open floor plan and soaring vaulted ceiling.  Low maintenance and beautiful floating stucco facade This home also features beautiful woodwork and many, many built-ins.  Brazilian cherry hardwood floors throughout, interspersed with tasteful carpet.  Two generous bedrooms up (each with its own full bath) and a large reading loft overlooking the great room.  Very large entertainment kitchen features first-quality stainless appliances (Subzero, double wall oven, 5-burner gas stove top), large walk-in pantry and an enormous granite island.  First floor also includes a floor-to-ceiling fireplace feature with gas fireplace, both casual and formal dining areas, large office, sunroom, laundry and mudroom. The master suite includes a very large main room and equally large bath, with Warm Tiles radiant heat, two walk-in closets, jetted bath, dual sinks and large two-head shower room. Basement was finished in 2008 and features Brazilian cherry flooring, a large bedroom with a large walk-in closet (with a sink!), a large open recreation room (convertible to a 5th bedroom), wet bar with wine/beverage cooler, a 3/4 bath, large media room (wired for surround sound), exercise room, craft/wrapping room, 300+ bottle wine room, and ample storage area (featuring 24' running feet of warehouse shelving).  The utility room includes a 100 gallon hot water heater (new in late 2014), two new furnaces for zone heating/cooling and ample storage/workshop space.  The backyard features an artificial-turf putting green and beautifully secluded relaxation space and pool deck. New screened-in gazebo in September 2016!  Multi-level terracing incudes waterfall and koi pond,  many perennial flowers and plants, tastefully decorative landscape lighting and a top level terrace area that is a giant sandbox (we use a portion as a fire pit).  Beautiful and ultra-low maintenance stucco that literally hangs off the house so as to eliminate any water intrusion issues with conventionally-applied stucco.  The pool includes an auto-cover, which safely and effectively keeps kids, animals and debris out and reduces maintenance and heating costs. New pool liner 2019!  The home is next to a full acre of play-friendly grassy outlot (owned and maintained by neighborhood association). Finally, the spacious 3-car garage includes built-ins, a workshop sink and (best of all) is heated! 

No selling agent calls accepted. We will sign one-day showing agreement with a Buyer agent at 2.5% of sales price.

description:
Recently sold: $440,000. Mature trees line the beautiful, winding streets of this sophisticated Mendota Heights neighborhood and welcome you home to 790 Evergreen Knolls. Nestled on a quiet street amongst other high end homes, this lovely home offers a top notch location, private lot and versatile floor plan with many updates! Come inside-

The foyer welcomes you inside and invites you to make yourself at home. A large sun-filled living room at the front of the house offers expansive views of the neighborhood while the formal dining room next door is perfect for hosting large dinner parties and gatherings!

Beautifully remodeled in 2014, this kitchen is truly the heart of this home. Gleaming granite countertops, high end stainless steel appliances, large center island and an open layout to the main level family room and sunroom/eat-in area will make this the most used area of your home! Invite friends and family over for get togethers in the large spaces or let the party spill out to the backyard deck. Overlooking the large wooded yard, you?ll have plenty of space and privacy for summer barbecues on the deck and patio!

Take a peek at the master bedroom down the hall ? with a private 3/4 bathroom, walk-in closet and convenient main floor location, you have tons of flexibility and options here. Need one level living? Everything you require can be found on the main level making this a home you can live in and stay in long term.

Need room for your growing family? Come upstairs! Two spacious and sun-filled bedrooms can be found in the upper level as well as a large bathroom. A third room is perfect for a nursery, home office, playroom or den.

Don?t forget about the finished basement! This huge space just awaits your movie and game nights, plus with easy access to the backyard patio, the options are endless. How will you use this space? Be sure to check out the large cedar closet and storage room ? attention to detail is evident even in the unfinished spaces!

Sophisticated, spacious, well-maintained and flexible are keywords when it comes to 790 Evergreen Knolls. Just move in and enjoy all that this home and prestigious neighborhood have to offer!

Recently sold: $510,000. Fantastic home on almost 3/4 acre in Mendota Heights! Cozy up beside multiple fireplaces during the colder months of the year or spend warm summer evenings on the back, maintenance-free deck that neighbors the expansive backyard. All four bedrooms await on the second level along with the laundry room, a master ensuite, and walk-in closet! Marie Park is just across the yard and lays claim to tennis courts, a baseball field, and lends to a quiet, natural feeling. Convenient location with easy access to either downtown, nearby Grand Avenue, and the International Airport! Don't miss the chance to call this home.
